The paper deals with trajectory optimization for unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of convex optimization and gradient optimization methods, which are commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of optimization to solve minimum-jerk trajectory problems, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications.
